node.text: @montymonsterslayer I don’t think you need to feel embarrassed at all honestly. I really admire your strength and respect you bc you’re a sweet soul who’s telling your story, and you have every right to tell it. Thank you for sharing this. I support you! 💪🏻⚡️

@isadorakosofsky sent me the rest of the pictures she took for the story today. After looking through the photos, dakota said "you really know how to close out a chapter in your life, beeb" ha.

They brought to light the support of my friends and chosen family. This chapter was one of those times that shows a person who thier real friends are, and aren't. 
Anyway the photos are compositionally breathtaking, each one telling a full story. And each of these, in particular, capture the depths of which each friend met me in this space where others couldn't.

🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤 I love you so much, my beautiful monster slayer. @isadorakosofsky captured these powerful moments so perfectly.
Incredibly powerful story, fantastic art. I hope you take over the world. 🙏🏻

@ntsengie I'm so sorry for the late reply; seeing this comment totally made me freeze. Some part of me is embarassed that the students I've modeled for know my very nsfw story but UM Y'ALL ARE FULL ASS ADULTS and if you resonate with the pain and realness of my story then I'm more than proud to share whatever bits give you healing, solidarity or inspire you to blaze trails and make some changes. Thank you for the genuine comment. It helped me reach down and meet you at the same level ✌🏼

@montymonsterslayer I don’t think you need to feel embarrassed at all honestly. I really admire your strength and respect you bc you’re a sweet soul who’s telling your story, and you have every right to tell it. Thank you for sharing this. I support you! 💪🏻⚡️

I deleted my first comment since they were just emojis “👏🏻❤️”, but after looking at the pics again I wanted to come back to say something more. Hey @montymonsterslayer , I’m one of Michael’s students at CLU who’s drawn/painted you before of models! I wanted to briefly say that you’re a stunning and strong woman who’s inspiring so many ppl more than you could ever know. So I’m here to say thank you, from me and the community who’s resonating with your story. I hope you’ll continue healing and bettering yourself more each day. Thanks for your bravery and openness. You rock! 💜
I'm so inspired by how you took this dark, terrible thing and created so much love and beauty.  Love you Steph!
Thank you for sharing your story with the world 🙏
naomi scott speechless song suits you I think
@visionsoflight_ miss you too. And you know me now. Seems like a pretty good time.
Miss you friend. That article only made me wish I knew you sooner. You're story is too inspiring. Until next time...
